'''元哲學'''（有時稱為'''哲學的哲學'''）是“對[[哲學|哲學]]本質的研究”。它的主題包括研究哲學的目的，哲學的邊界及[[哲學方法論|研究方法]]。<ref name=Joll>{{cite web |encyclopedia=Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy (IEP) |url=http://www.iep.utm.edu/con-meta/ |title=Contemporary Metaphilosophy |author=Nicholas Joll |date=November 18, 2010 |access-date=2020-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110805114836/http://www.iep.utm.edu/con-meta/ |archive-date=2011-08-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name=Marsoobian>{{cite book |chapter=Metaphilosophy |title=American Philosophy: An Encyclopedia |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KmUTkreTEQsC&pg=PA500 |pages=500–501 |quote=Its primary question is "''What is philosophy?''" |author=Armen T Marsoobian |editor1=John Lachs |editor2=Robert Talisse |isbn=978-0203492796 |year=2004 |access-date=2020-06-17 |archive-date=2013-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618001557/http://books.google.com/books?id=KmUTkreTEQsC&pg=PA500 |dead-url=no }}</ref>因此，儘管哲學探究存在的本質、客觀的現實、知識的可能性、[[真理|真理]]的本質等，但元哲學卻是對本質、目的和方法的進行自我反思性的探究。透過詢問什麼是哲學的本身、它應該問什麼樣的問題、通過提出和回答提問以及在實現過程中可以體驗什麼來進行此類探究。一些人認為它是哲學的先驅和預備課<ref name=Griswold>而另一些人則將其固有地視為哲學的一部分 {{cite book |title=Platonic Writings/Platonic Readings |author=[http://www.bu.edu/philo/people/faculty/full-time/charles-l-griswold/ Charles L. Griswold Jr.] |isbn=978-0271044811 |publisher=Penn State Press |year=2010 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZCB33OPRE-AC&pg=PA146 |pages=144–146 |access-date=2020-06-17 |archive-date=2020-07-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200701234920/https://books.google.com/books?id=ZCB33OPRE-AC&pg=PA146 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，或自動將其視為哲學的一部分，而另一些人則將這些觀點結合在一起。<ref name=Williamson>{{cite book |author=Timothy Williamson |title=The Philosophy of Philosophy |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |year=2008 |chapter=Preface |page=ix |quote=The philosophy of philosophy is automatically part of philosophy, just as the philosophy of anything else is... |isbn=978-0470695913 |chapter-url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YN2KGBgKwOcC&pg=PR9 |access-date=2020-06-17 |archive-date=2020-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914201713/https://books.google.com/books?id=YN2KGBgKwOcC&pg=PR9 |dead-url=no }}</ref>
